BASIC INFO
==========

in windows, just run `build.bat`, and a visual studio project will be created, 
then double-click 'myADT.sln' to build the solution

in linux/unix, 
> mkdir build
> cd build
> cmake .. -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=where-to-install
> make ; make install
(Debug or Release)


OPTIONS
=======
-DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=where-to-install    specify the path to install the library
-DDO_CHECK=ON                              enable checking, e.g. if passed null pointer
                                           or index out of range etc.
-DBUILD_SHARED=ON                          enable building shared library
